        <mxCell id="ayJMt9I-cEMU8xtIQuHl-20" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="private S3 bucket for static files (outside the vpc, access for cloudfront using OAC - origin access control).&lt;div&gt;bucket policy - only cloudfront with sigv4 signature has access to the private bucket&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="180" x="-42" y="240" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ayJMt9I-cEMU8xtIQuHl-19" edge="1" parent="1" source="cf" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0;exitY=0.21;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;exitPerimeter=0;entryX=1;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;" target="ayJMt9I-cEMU8xtIQuHl-16">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="140" y="210" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ayJMt9I-cEMU8xtIQuHl-21" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Github Actions Pipeline&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;1) GitHub runner setup&lt;/b&gt; - downloading the source code and installing the required python environment (Python 3.10).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;2) code scanning (Linting - flake8)&lt;/b&gt; - static code scanning for syntax errors before building the docker image.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;3) Build &amp;amp; Container Scanning (Docker + Trivy)&lt;/b&gt; - building the docker image and scanning it before pushing to AWS: ensures no vulnerable OS packages are introduced to your ECS cluster.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;4) Secure AWS Authentication (OIDC)&lt;/b&gt; - instead of pushing the images to AWS using hard-coded access keys, we&#39;ll use OIDC which uses temporary signed tokens for pipeline runs.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;5) Pushing to AWS&lt;/b&gt; - the pipeline pushes the image to ECR, the static files to S3, updates the ECS Fargate orchestrator and clears the CloudFront cache.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;6) ECS Deployment &amp;amp; Cache Invalidation&lt;/b&gt; - update the task definition with the new docker image tag, and deploy it to the Fargate cluster. Finally, execute a CloudFront invalidation so users instantly see any CSS or image changes you made.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="540" x="-550" y="440" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
